---
title: Fig and Rosemary New York Strip Steak with Fingerling Potatoes and Asparagus
description: A strip steak is a triumph in itself, known for its tenderness and marbling. But to make it truly extraordinary, it helps to have some powerhouse accompaniments. Here, that’s a trifecta of fig jam, balsamic glaze, and rosemary. The jam brings deep, full-bodied sweetness. The balsamic adds a jolt of tart electricity. And the rosemary unleashes a wave of alluring herb-y aromas. When swirled together in a sauce, that translates into big flavors that match the gusto of the meat.
